## Survey Creation
![Survey Creation image](https://github.com/formbricks/design/assets/94018985/69d63121-5999-4ccb-a51c-a43c0a546b1d)
- [ ] 11. ðŸŸ Each question has several buttons (Next Question/Previous Question/Copy Question/Delete Question) in the top-right that aren't focusable via key commands. Tab should cycle through these buttons.
- [ ] 12. ðŸŸ The Delete button and Add Option button (+) next to every free-text field should be tab-focusable (currently they are not).
- [ ] 13. ðŸŸ¡Focus state for "Add Logic" button should show tooltip descriptor.
- [ ] 14. ðŸŸ When tabbing to an existing, unselected question, you're not able to open the question menu with key commands. After focusing on it with Tab, you should be able to push the question menu open with the Enter key.
- [ ] 15. ðŸŸ Add Question CTA is not focusable via the Tab key.
- [ ] 16. ðŸŸ¡Selecting a Call-to-Action type or Terms and Conditions type question resets your current Tab navigation spot to the top of the page instead of setting it to the next contained focusable element, like other question types.
- [ ] 17. ðŸŸ¡In Rating-type questions, focusing on the drop-downs via Tab isn't indicated via a focus state even though it's added. Create a more prominent focus state for these elements.
- [ ] 18. ðŸŸ¡**Preview window** - Rating scale should be Tab-focusable, and its suboptions should be focusable via arrow keys.
- [ ] 19. ðŸŸ¡**Preview window** - Radio buttons should be Tab-focusable.
- [ ] 20. ðŸŸ¡**Preview window** - Checkboxes should be Tab-focusable.
- [ ] 21. ðŸŸ¡Settings sections should be Tab-focusable (currently only the sub-elements are Tab-focusable). Sub-elements should then me made focusable via the arrow keys.
- [ ] 22. ðŸŸ¡When Tab-focusing on sub-elements currently, you can't get back out to the primary links with Shift+Tab, you have to Tab all the way through to the primary links at the beginning of the page.

## Responses
![Responses image](https://github.com/formbricks/design/assets/94018985/97c32a0c-cfbd-4d82-bf6c-575862fcd2a4)
- [ ] 23. ðŸŸ¡**Filters** - When creating a new filter, the question type selector drop-down isn't openable via the key commands. Arrow keys should open the drop-down in this instance (since Enter key is expected to perform a search).
- [ ] 24. ðŸŸ¡**Filters** - After selecting a question type, the subsequent fields are not openable via key commands, nor is the Delete button for the filter line you created.
- [ ] 25. ðŸŸ¡Downloads drop-down should be Tab-focusable.
- [ ] 26. ðŸŸ **Responses tab** - Note button for a single response is not focusable via key commands. Tab should pull you to the + button here.
- [ ] 27. ðŸŸ¡**Responses tab** - After creating a Note, you can't select the delete (-) key via Tab or Shift+Tab. It should be Tab-focusable.
